em>《守望先锋 2》</em>中上线之前，将《守望先锋》叙事中许多不同的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2016-12-21-russia-bans-overwatch-comic-for-being-gay-propaganda.html">跨媒体线索</a>联系在一起。第一集将于<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dota-netflix-anime-012543673.html">7 月 6 日在 YouTube 上发布</a>，时长仅五分多钟。</p><p>多年来，《守望先锋》粉丝们一直在乞求一部基于该系列的<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-17-rumors-resurface-diablo-overwatch-animated-series.html">节目</a>甚至电影。这部迷你剧可能是目前为止最接近的，但谁知道呢？如果事实证明它足够受欢迎，暴雪可能会被说服投资一个更大的项目，将《守望先锋》宇宙呈现在全新的观众面前。与此同时， <em>《守望先锋 2》</em>游戏总监亚伦·凯勒 (Aaron Keller)<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://overwatch.blizzard.com/en-us/news/23968777/">表示</a>，游戏的每个故事任务都将有一个开场和结束动画，以帮助阐明更多的叙事内容。</p><p>丰富而令人难忘的角色阵容在原版<em>《守望先锋》</em>于 2016 年首次亮相时成为一种文化现象方面发挥了重要作用。如果暴雪能够成功地再次将聚光灯更加明亮地聚焦在他们身上，这可能会帮助粉丝们原谅工作室<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/overwatch-2-director-explains-why-hero-missions-were-canceled-211629105.html">的一些错误</a>最近在<em>《守望先锋 2》</em>中<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/krisholt/2023/06/17/overwatch-2s-pve-story-missions-paywall-is-another-self-inflicted-body-blow/">犯下的</a><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/overwatch-2-director-explains-why-hero-missions-were-canceled-211629105.html">错误</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/an-overwatch-anime-miniseries-will-debut-on-july-6th-203026390.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/an-overwatch-anime-miniseries-will-debut-on-july-6th-203026390.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7e1b968b-865b-4fc2-8b03-58b524a8b1fb</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2023 20:30:26 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688156364</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T20:19:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="793" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/425bb330-1781-11ee-af7f-e7b774ba2c13" width="1638"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="793" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/425bb330-1781-11ee-af7f-e7b774ba2c13" width="1638"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Blizzard Entertainment]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A young Torbjörn commands turrets in the Overwatch animated miniseries 'Genesis.']]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Torbjörn in Overwatch animated miniseries 'Genesis.']]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Sony didn’t want ‘Roblox’ on PlayStation due to child safety concerns]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>索尼在 PlayStation 游戏机上屏蔽了<em>Roblox，</em>因为它担心儿童会接触到不当内容。这一爆料来自<em>Axios</em>首次<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.axios.com/2023/06/29/playstation-roblox-jim-ryan">报道的</a>2022 年文件，该文件是在<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ftc-expected-to-file-injunction-to-block-microsofts-purchase-of-activision-blizzard-165738788.html">FTC 对微软的审判</a>中发现的。然而，索尼互动娱乐公司总裁兼首席执行官 Jim Ryan 当时表示，该公司的立场正在软化，为这个病毒式用户生成平台的最终 PlayStation 端口敞开了大门。</p><p> Ryan 在去年初向投资者解释了拒绝<em>Roblox 的</em>决定。 “从历史上看，由于有大量儿童在 PlayStation 上玩，我们一直非常小心地防止他们接触任何可能利用他们的东西，”他当时说道。但他对渴望在索尼游戏机上看到<em>Roblox 的</em>投资者表现出了乐观的态度。 “然而，在过去几年里，我们审查了这些政策，并在这方面放松了一些。我们已经保守太久了，现在我们正在与<em>Roblox 的</em>人接触。我们希望情况能够改变。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>尽管一年多前就发表了上述评论，但<em>Roblox</em>仍然没有出现在 PlayStation 游戏机上。这款深受喜爱的游戏可让用户创建、共享和播放用户创建的内容，适用于 Xbox、iOS、Android、Windows 和 macOS。任天堂尚未就<em>《Roblox</em> 》无法在 Switch 上推出一事发表评论，但这家游戏机制造商历来也犯了谨慎的错误，不让儿童接触到不当内容。</p><p> <em>Roblox</em>于 2021 年推出了<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roblox-content-ratings-system-195640367.html">内容分级系统，</a>以帮助家长更好地控制孩子玩的用户创建的游戏。该平台超过一半的日常用户年龄在 13 岁以下。尽管该平台禁止展示性活动、非法物质和脏话的内容，但偶尔的违规内容可能会在用户创建的标题中逃脱审核。此外， <em>Roblox</em>正在努力<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roblox-now-allows-creators-to-build-content-for-people-17-and-older-195024163.html">留住用户的</a>成长，现在允许 17 岁及以上的玩家观看内容。该公司表示，17 至 24 岁年龄段是<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://blog.roblox.com/2023/05/our-vision-for-all-ages/">增长最快的群体</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/sony-didnt-want-roblox-on-playstation-due-to-child-safety-concerns-200631635.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/sony-didnt-want-roblox-on-playstation-due-to-child-safety-concerns-200631635.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> baf7af65-6e9d-4f66-b86b-7c01f00321c5</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2023 20:06:31 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688155593</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T20:06:38+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Finance - Lifestyle]]></category><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Game Consoles]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/442ad540-177e-11ee-8dfd-38cb91e04d8a" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/442ad540-177e-11ee-8dfd-38cb91e04d8a" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Roblox]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A marketing image for Robox, featuring virtual children and teenagers dancing on a floor with a disco ball overhead.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Roblox dance]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The FTC plans to slap companies with hefty fines for using fake reviews]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>联邦贸易委员会（<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/ftc/">联邦贸易委员会</a></ins>） 有<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.ftc.gov/system/files/ftc_gov/pdf/r311003consumerreviewsandtestimonials_nprm.pdf">提出正式禁令</a></ins>关于虚假评论和推荐。如果该规则按现行规定生效，公司还将被禁止使用虚假的关注者和观点来夸大其社交媒体指标。</p><p>这并不是该机构第一次将目光瞄准虚假评论。第一次出现这样的情况<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-02-27-ftc-cracks-down-on-fake-amazon-reviews-in-landmark-case.html">2019年</a></ins>，它对第三方亚马逊卖家支付虚假评论的罚款（亚马逊本身也有<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2015-04-09-amazon-fake-review-lawsuit.html">起诉虚假评论提供商</a></ins>）。今年早些时候，FTC 对一个维生素品牌所有者处以 60 万美元的罚款<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ftc-fines-supplement-maker-600000-for-review-hijacking-amazon-listings-210142185.html">亚马逊上的“评论劫持”</a></ins> 。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该机构表示正在制定新规则<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/news/press-releases/2022/10/ftc-explore-rulemaking-combat-fake-reviews-other-deceptive-endorsements">在十月</a></ins>，即将敲定，其中包括对那些被发现兜售虚假评论和推荐的人的严厉处罚。作为<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2023/06/30/fake-reviews-online-ftc/"><em>华盛顿邮报</em></a></ins>指出，FTC 计划对“购买、出售和操纵在线评论”的企业处以最高 5 万美元的处罚。这不仅适用于每条虚假评论，也适用于消费者每次看到它。因此，如果 FTC 发现一条虚假评论仅被浏览了 20 次，那么购买该评论的企业可能会承担 100 万美元的责任。</p><p> “我们针对虚假评论提出的规则表明，我们正在使用一切可用的手段来攻击数字时代的欺骗性广告，”联邦贸易委员会消费者保护局局长塞缪尔·莱文在一份声明中表示。 “该规则将对违规者引发民事处罚，并应有助于为诚实的公司提供公平的竞争环境。”</p><p>明确地说，联邦贸易委员会的目标是禁止“企业撰写或销售由不存在的人、没有产品或服务经验或歪曲其经历的人撰写或销售的消费者评论或推荐”。同样，公司也不得获得或传播他们“知道或应该知道是假的”的评论和推荐。</p><p>重新利用现有评论，使其看起来像是为不同产品撰写的（即评论劫持），以及为正面或负面评论提供付款或其他形式的补偿，都将被禁止。联邦贸易委员会表示，公司仍然可以要求用户留下评论，因为这是小企业提高声誉的重要途径。</p><p>在没有明确披露的情况下，经理和管理人员不得发布对其公司产品的评论，在某些情况下也不能要求家庭成员或员工这样做。根据拟议的规则，公司将不被允许运营声称对包括其自己的产品和服务类别提供独立评论的网站。</p><p>评论压制也将被禁止。公司不得使用恐吓手段（例如法律威胁和虚假指控）来迫使客户删除或避免留下负面评论。</p><p>此外，联邦贸易委员会还试图禁止公司使用虚假粉丝和观点来虚报其社交媒体数量。该机构表示：“拟议的规则还将禁止任何人购买此类指标，以歪曲其对商业目的的重要性。”这项规定可能会产生超出商业范围的深远影响——影响者可能必须确保他们在试图获得品牌交易时不会考虑机器人。</p><p>与此同时，拟议的规则通知注意到了<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/generative-ai/">生成式人工智能</a></ins>。 “据报道，人工智能聊天机器人被用来创建虚假评论，”它写道。 “正如报告指出的那样，人工智能聊天机器人的广泛出现可能会让不良行为者更容易撰写虚假评论。”</p><p>该规则不会立即生效。该指令将在 60 天的时间内公开征求公众意见，之后该机构将在最终确定该指令之前考虑更改。</p><p>其中很多规定都是有道理的。从本质上讲，联邦贸易委员会正在努力确保企业和品牌对消费者透明和诚实。然而，实际执行这些措施却是另一回事。该机构告诉《<em>华盛顿邮报》</em> ，它不会获得额外的资源来打击虚假评论的提供者，但成文的规则可以增强其在法庭上的影响力。对付销售和发布虚假评论的海外公司可能也是一项艰巨的任务。尽管如此，对这些做法的正式禁止以及令人瞠目结舌的罚款威胁可能足以阻止一些公司使用虚假评论。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-ftc-plans-to-slap-companies-with-hefty-fines-for-using-fake-reviews-192833691.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-ftc-plans-to-slap-companies-with-hefty-fines-for-using-fake-reviews-192833691.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> b58adbf2-2d2b-4ba1-a106-1028b8241566</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2023 19:28:33 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688153314</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T19:28:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Business]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government Agencies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="4172" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/2be9e870-177b-11ee-9fe6-3ecf0a6aab7e" width="6337"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4172" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/2be9e870-177b-11ee-9fe6-3ecf0a6aab7e" width="6337"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - In this April 17, 2019, file photo, online customer reviews for a product are displayed on a computer in New York. The Federal Trade Commission on Friday, June 30, 2023, proposed a new rule that would ban paying for reviews, suppressing honest reviews, selling fake social media engagement and more. The FTC noted that it already considers fake reviews and other deceptive actions to be unlawful — but that the new bans “may increase deterrence against these practices,” allow for civil penalties and help get financial compensation to victims, the agency said. (AP Photo/Jenny Kane, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Fake Review Ban Proposal]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[This nifty fan-made Game Boy camera is the size of a cartridge]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>官方的 Game Boy 相机对于低保真摄影爱好者来说是一种享受，但它的尺寸也更大，从复古控制台中突出，就像一个巨大的、令人毛骨悚然的眼球。这就是为什么改装者和超级粉丝 Christopher Graves 制作了他自己的版本——Game Boy Mini Camera， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://gizmodo.com/brilliantly-modded-game-boy-camera-is-no-bigger-than-a-1850595045">正如<em>Gizmodo 最初报道的那样。</em></a>这个东西很小，因为格雷夫斯设法将所有东西缩小到游戏机卡带的大小，并且不需要突出。</p><p>格雷夫斯使用定制板、原始相机的传感器、内存映射控制器和一些电容器来完成该项目。他还使用了 iPhone XR 的镜头，将其拧入定制套筒中，以将突出量降至最低。尽管该镜头会改变位置以适应新类型的拍摄，但它根本不会影响质量。换句话说，即使在 25 年后，您仍然可以看到原始 Game Boy 相机如此受欢迎的颗粒状黑白外观。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>相机滑入卡带插槽，甚至可以运行 ROMS（如果您有的话）。它还通过闪存进行了升级，因此您存储的照片可以永远保存（或直到驱动器耗尽）。格雷夫斯计划改进设计，因为他正在考虑用 iPhone 14 镜头替换 iPhone XR 镜头等选项。 </p><div id="92baccef7b74492983f2eb2128b84dff"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Videoooo - 请忽略任何令人尴尬的部分，谢谢<a href="https://t.co/ux5mKmcII9">pic.twitter.com/ux5mKmcII9</a></p> — @gameboycamera@glitch.lgbt (@thegameboycam) <a href="https://twitter.com/thegameboycam/status/1674609897009184768?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 6 月 30 日</a></blockquote></div><p>这里真正的好处是小型化。例如，当连接到 Game Boy Pocket 时，整个东西实际上可以放入口袋中，从而使您免于不得不坐着听“或者您只是很高兴见到我”的愚蠢笑话。</p><p>当然，这是一个由一个人完成的 DIY 项目，所以先不要打开支票簿。自 20 世纪 90 年代末初代 Game Boy 相机推出以来，小型化技术已经取得了多么大的进步，这一点仍然令人惊叹。如果创作者的名字听起来很熟悉，他还将标准的 Game Boy 相机改装成了<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/game-boy-camera-mirrorless-camera-conversion-162844001.html">现代的无反光镜版本。</a>复古爱好者当然知道他的东西。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/this-nifty-fan-made-game-boy-camera-is-the-size-of-a-cartridge-185209536.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/this-nifty-fan-made-game-boy-camera-is-the-size-of-a-cartridge-185209536.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9d2db4c1-4034-4a74-baef-1ce98c0d6ce2</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2023 18:52:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688151697</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T19:01:40+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="1403" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/721817c0-1778-11ee-bff7-fc5d09947f62" width="2048"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1403" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/721817c0-1778-11ee-bff7-fc5d09947f62" width="2048"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Christopher Graves ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Game Boy Mini Cera next to original camera and a large lens.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Game Boy Mini Cera]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best passive bookshelf speakers for most people]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>黑胶唱片的复兴已经有一段时间了，而这场流行病在某种程度上只是加速了这一趋势。许多人希望从廉价的 Crosley 转盘升级并构建他们的第一个 HiFi 系统。当然，构建一个像样的立体声音响需要多个部件，但也许最重要的是扬声器。如果您的扬声器听起来不好，那么将它们连接到什么基本上并不重要。</p><h2>有源扬声器与无源扬声器</h2><p>可以理解的是，这是人们可能花费最多时间研究的设置部分。而且你必须做出很多选择。最大的问题之一是：主动还是被动？两种类型的扬声器都有其优点，但为了本指南的目的，我们将重点关注无源扬声器，它需要单独的放大器。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>有源扬声器具有内置放大器。通常，这两件事是专门设计来协同工作的，这意味着您将获得更忠实的制造商听觉视觉版本。而且由于您不需要外部放大器，因此有源扬声器占用的空间也更少。虽然有源扬声器比无源扬声器更昂贵，但您需要购买放大器来为无源扬声器供电，这意味着节省的成本并不像最初看起来那么大。被动的主要好处是更大的灵活性。您无法出去购买自己的放大器并将有源扬声器连接到它；此外，由于有源扬声器需要电源，因此您必须确保它们位于插座附近。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-06/c3049351-d9bf-11eb-ae7f-fe41bc844706" alt="无源书架式扬声器指南"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">特伦斯·奥布莱恩/Engadget</div></figure><p>我们还对本指南的支出设定了上限：600 美元，有些随意。除此之外，您就开始进入预算发烧友的领域。它还基本上将我们限制在五到六英寸之间的书架扬声器上。虽然您当然可以花这么多钱购买落地式扬声器，但在相同价位的书架式扬声器上，驱动器的质量可能会更好。</p><h2>关于测试的注意事项</h2><p>显然，我无法测试 600 美元以下的<em>每套</em>5 到 6 英寸书架扬声器，但我已经进行了足够的尝试并进行了足够的研究，对我的建议充满信心。我确信还有其他好的扬声器系统，但我认为没有人会后悔购买这里的套装。</p><p>此外，说话者的偏好在很大程度上是主观的。但我尽力做到尽可能客观。所有扬声器都连接到具有相同电线输入的 Pyle PSS6 切换器，以便快速并排比较。在我亲自测试完它们之后，我招募了多个人盲目地聆听，然后根据他们的偏好对它们进行排名，看看他们的观点是否与我自己的一致。测试包括播放新的和老式的黑胶唱片，以及来自 Spotify 的流媒体歌曲。</p><p>另外值得注意的是：我不是发烧友。这不是针对发烧友的指南。我希望我的音乐听起来不错，但我不打算降低我的立体声音响上的二手轿车的价格。我的设置包括一个 Audio Technica Audio-Technica AT-LP120 和一个通过 Technics SA-EX110 运行的 Chromecast Audio。这不是什么花哨的东西，但它肯定是对 Crosley Suitcase 转盘甚至更高端的 Sonos 音响系统的升级。</p><h2>最适合大多数人：Audioengine HDP6</h2><p><core-commerce id="2a672d2f58294bc4814f89960338fbd9" data-type="product-list"></p><p>老实说，我测试过的很多扬声器听起来都非常相似。但不是<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfHTEMbMttPF_8JHtUsc6hLZdtO_SGfnsYG4E5RAh8tW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAudioengine-Passive-Bookshelf-Stand-mount-Speakers%2Fdp%2FB01LMJ2NY8">399 美元的 Audioengines</a> 。除了昂贵得多的 KEF 对之外，它们的声音比所有其他产品都要明亮得多、清晰度要高得多。我尝试过的这双耳机还采用了华丽的“胡桃木”外壳，这有助于它们在实用的黑色海洋中脱颖而出。</p><p> HDP6 提供特别强劲的中音，在人声和吉他方面表现出色。但它们在整个频谱上听起来相当平衡。像《九寸钉》《The Day the Whole World Went Away》这样的高耸作品变得栩栩如生，并揭示了一些细微差别，坦率地说，我以前从未在耳机上注意到过这些细微差别。 Floating Points、Pharoah Sanders 和伦敦交响乐团最近推出的专辑<em>《Promises》</em>是如此的包罗万象，让我想把我现在的落地式扬声器扔进垃圾桶。</p><p>虽然书架式扬声器本身无法提供落地式扬声器或低音炮所能提供的震撼房间的重击声，但 HDP6 在播放低音重歌曲时表现出色。他们没有我的测试设备中的最低端，但鼓和贝斯仍然强劲而清晰。</p><h2>对于那些想要最好的声音的人：KEF Q150</h2><p><core-commerce id="d717853708a74d86bbc8a1b585085caa" data-type="product-list"></p><p>如果您最关心的是音质，而不考虑其他因素，请查看<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Crutchfield;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3c3db68e-8b44-47ba-9267-2a00d1409126&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Crutchfield&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcwyxFR43_HrsJeRlKUM1Z5EJ4M6wBSvFFfSoXLsMpLv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crutchfield.com%2FS-hvdISrfpdhs%2Fp_991Q150B%2FKEF-Q150-Black.html">Q150s</a> 。这些是著名发烧友品牌 KEF 的入门级选择，也是在我的盲品测试中唯一击败 Audioengines 的扬声器。它们并不是每次都名列前茅，有些人在两者之间做出选择时遇到了困难，但最终我认为 KEF 在纯音质方面略有优势。他们在频谱的极低端和高端有更多的音量。它为 Beach Boys 的“Wouldnt it Be Nice”等曲目增添了一定的亮点，而 Run the Jewels 的“JU$T”则比 HDP6 的打击力稍重一些。根据您所听的内容，差异可能很细微，但在并排测试中这是不可否认的。</p><p> KEF 的音频配置文件与 Audioengines 的音频配置文件类似。与本综述中的所有其他扬声器设置相比，它们都更明亮，并且具有更多的高音和中音。如果您喜欢用高品质黑胶唱片聆听古典音乐或爵士乐，这些将提供您正在寻找的频率响应。</p><p> Q150 未能名列前茅的原因是其标价。它们的价格为 600 美元，基本上与我测试过的最昂贵的扬声器持平。 （ <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Crutchfield;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3c3db68e-8b44-47ba-9267-2a00d1409126&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Crutchfield&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAaC4DX_C71qU-iogB8qtrLN4cRCmp2RtYPr2VWuCMtat&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crutchfield.com%2FS-oP5GBt6Z5y3%2Fp_107RSV100%2FPolk-Audio-Reserve-R100-Midnight-Black.html">Polk R100s 的</a>售价为 599 美元，但没有进入最终淘汰名单。）虽然 Q150s 听起来比 HDP6 稍好一些，但它们不一定比 HDP6 贵 200 美元。然而，在撰写本文时，Q150 的售价为 400 美元，这使它们成为 Audioengines 的一个引人注目的选择。</p><h2>对于讨价还价的人来说：JBL A130</h2><p><core-commerce id="9e5f425a9a5f487d816e292d02920649" data-type="product-list"></p><p>在听众偏好方面， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Crutchfield;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3c3db68e-8b44-47ba-9267-2a00d1409126&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Crutchfield&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZgP0261Rv0ewK2AdedpAL0wZmVHlu_iEiTGRwR_0EAn&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crutchfield.com%2FS-jBsFxyaQ1kQ%2Fp_109SA130AM%2FJBL-Stage-A130.html">JBL</a>一直处于中间位置。它们不像 KEF 和 Audioengines 那样明亮，但在低端也不像 Polk S15 那样浑浊。如果您只是在寻找一套像样的扬声器并且不关心规格表，或者如果您主要听流媒体音乐并且只是偶尔放上黑胶唱片，那么如果您能找到它们打折的话，这些都是不错的选择。</p><h2>对于那些需要更多低音的人：ELAC ​​Debut 2.0 DB6.2</h2><p><core-commerce id="8ddf9a4261b74a178f1dec49a37cca23" data-type="product-list"></p><p>好吧，这些扬声器有点违反了我们的规则，但是，如果您选择稍大的 6.5 英寸 DB6.2，而不是 DB5.2，您会在底端听到更多的重击声。在清晰度方面， <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcFv8U-y-GyQnuFcdJ0aVBKVKwBa-WTFsNLD6GbxrM0L&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FELAC-Debut-Bookshelf-Speakers-Black%2Fdp%2FB07B4Q5587">Debuts</a>无法完全与 Audioengine 或 KEF 相媲美，但您会感觉到每个 808 的打击感要强得多。 Backxwash 的新专辑<em>《I Lie Here Buried with my Rings and my Dresses》</em>在 ELAC ​​上的表现比在 Polks、JBL 甚至 KEF 上更猛烈。而且它们只花费 350 美元，这还不错。</p><p>如果您主要听电子音乐和现代嘻哈音乐，您可以考虑 Debut 2.0 DB6.2。</p><h2>对于那些想忽略我的建议的人：</h2><p>如果您找不到打折的 JBL A130，并且确实想尽可能省钱，您可以购买<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Crutchfield;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3c3db68e-8b44-47ba-9267-2a00d1409126&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Crutchfield&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAR_h3353TjxEprhrUQ4sxZCcEBoY4-A1LkeFV1nHxRuX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crutchfield.com%2FS-5Z8UtxCM9Dd%2Fp_107SIGS15%2FPolk-Audio-Signature-S15-Washed-Black-Walnut.html%3F">Polk S15</a> 。 S15 听起来<em>不错</em>，但 JBL 绝对更胜一筹。它们的音场不如我测试过的其他扬声器那么深，而且低音可能有点不确定。这些可能比立体声系统更适合作为家庭影院系统的一部分。标价 229 美元的它们可能看起来很便宜，但我会节省你的钱多花一点时间，然后去买更好的东西。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Crutchfield;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3c3db68e-8b44-47ba-9267-2a00d1409126&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Crutchfield&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATSnEZdReN1_p_H2ejF22K4Kj1F_2ZYK3xn7j7zF0WtP&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crutchfield.com%2FS-lyiSELh2W75%2Fp_107RSV100%2FPolk-Audio-Reserve-R100-Midnight-Black.html%3F">Polk R100</a>是听起来不错的扬声器。也许比 JBL 稍好一些，尽管声音配置更接近 Polk 自己的 S15。问题是它们的价格是 600 美元，与我测试过的最贵的一样。以一半的价格，这些可能是一个不错的选择，但每个测试者对 600 美元的 KEF 和 400 美元的 Audioengine 的排名都高于 R100。</p><p>我毫不怀疑<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcNjXjsJCMeTErmXuCKKg-3iA7Gd4LSFKHA4AHfnH6HT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAcoustics-3020i-Bookshelf-Speaker-Graphite%2Fdp%2FB07C4V26N1%3F">这些</a>都是非常好的扬声器：它们是目前<em>Wirecutter</em>的首选。但我无法测试它们，因此无法为它们提供担保。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-best-passive-bookshelf-speakers-under-600-dollars-for-most-people-140057354.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-best-passive-bookshelf-speakers-under-600-dollars-for-most-people-140057354.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> fbc75bf0-9cde-49f1-a066-0743b2bc4a72</guid><dc:creator>泰伦斯·奥布莱恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2023 18:30:04 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688149804</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T18:30:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Speakers & Headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Shopping]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Terrence O&#39;Brien]]></category><media:content height="1152" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-06/c304e170-d9bf-11eb-bd67-9645d103c50e" width="2048"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1152" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-06/c304e170-d9bf-11eb-bd67-9645d103c50e" width="2048"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Terrence O'Brien / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Passive Bookshelf Speaker Guide]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Passive Bookshelf Speaker Guide]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[AI pioneer Geoffrey Hinton isn't convinced good AI will triumph over bad AI]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>多伦多大学教授杰弗里·辛顿 (Geoffrey Hinton) 通常被称为“<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/godfather-of-ai-leaves-google-amid-ethical-concerns-152451800.html">人工智能教父</a></ins>由于他在神经网络方面的开创性研究，他最近成为了该行业的非官方监管者。今年春天，他辞去了谷歌的工作，以便更自由地批评他帮助开创的领域。他看到了最近生成式人工智能的激增，比如<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-is-suddenly-everywhere-are-we-ready-180031821.html">聊天GPT</a></ins>和<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-new-bing-edge-ai-copilot-hands-on-demo-test-chatgpt-openai-213332455.html">必应聊天</a></ins>作为发展不受控制且具有潜在危险的加速的迹象。与此同时，谷歌似乎放弃了之前的克制，推出了类似产品来追逐竞争对手。<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-bard-ai-hands-on-a-work-in-progress-with-plenty-of-caveats-170956025.html">吟游诗人聊天机器人</a></ins>。</p><p>在本周于多伦多举行的碰撞会议上，Hinton 扩大了他的担忧。当各家公司都在宣传人工智能是解决从签订租赁到运输货物等各种问题的解决方案时，Hinton 却敲响了警钟。他不相信好的人工智能会战胜坏的人工智能，而且他认为人工智能的道德采用可能会付出高昂的代价。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2>对人类的威胁</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/01698cc0-176e-11ee-b7be-cb0ddef17bed" style="height:1280px;width:1920px;" alt="杰弗里·辛顿 (Geoffrey Hinton) 出席 2023 年碰撞大赛" data-uuid="64c323f2-4fa9-3211-95ba-4b6d02ef062e"><figcaption>多伦多大学教授 Geoffrey Hinton（左）在 Collision 2023 上发表讲话。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">乔恩·芬加斯/Engadget 摄</div></figure><h2></h2><p>Hinton 认为，人工智能的好坏取决于创造它的人，而糟糕的技术仍然可能胜出。他解释说：“我不相信一个试图阻止坏事的好的人工智能能够控制住我。”可能很难阻止军工联合体生产<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017-07-25-will-we-be-able-to-control-the-killer-robots-of-tomorrow.html">战斗机器人</a></ins>例如，他说——公司和军队可能“喜欢”战争，其中伤亡的是可以轻松更换的机器。虽然 Hinton 认为大型语言模型（经过训练的人工智能可以生成类似人类的文本，例如<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/openai-just-released-gpt-4-a-multi-modal-generative-ai-172326765.html">OpenAI 的 GPT-4</a></ins> ）可能会导致生产力的大幅提高，但他担心统治阶级可能会利用这一点来充实自己，从而扩大本已巨大的贫富差距。辛顿说，这将“让富人更富，穷人更穷”。</p><p> Hinton 还重申了他广为人知的观点，即人工智能可以<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ai-presents-risk-of-extinction-on-par-with-nuclear-war-industry-leaders-say-114025874.html">构成生存风险</a></ins>对人类。如果人工智能变得比人类更聪明，就不能保证人类仍能掌控一切。 Hinton 表示，如果人工智能认为需要控制才能实现其目标，“我们就有麻烦了”。对他来说，威胁“不仅仅是科幻小说”；必须认真对待它们。他担心社会只有在有机会看到杀手机器人“到底有多可怕”之后才会对其进行控制。</p><p> Hinton 补充说，目前还存在很多问题。他认为<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-newest-ai-fairness-benchmark-measures-even-more-granular-bias-markers-140043320.html">偏见和歧视</a></ins>问题仍然存在，因为人工智能训练数据的偏差可能会产生不公平的结果。算法同样创造<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017-05-05-facebook-topics-to-follow-news-feed-fake-news.html">回声室</a></ins>加剧错误信息和心理健康问题。辛顿还担心人工智能会在这些房间之外传播错误信息。他不确定是否有可能抓住每一个虚假声明，尽管“将所有假货标记为假货很重要”。</p><p>这并不是说 Hinton 对人工智能的影响感到绝望，尽管他警告说，健康地使用该技术可能会付出高昂的代价。人类可能必须进行“实证工作”来了解人工智能如何出错，并防止它夺取控制权。他补充说，纠正偏见已经是“可行的”。大型语言模型人工智能可能会终结回音室，但 Hinton 认为公司政策的变化尤为重要。</p><p>这位教授在回答有关人们因自动化而失业的问题时毫不拐弯抹角。他认为需要“社会主义”来解决不平等问题，人们可以通过从事可能随时间变化的职业来避免失业，比如管道工（不，他不是在开玩笑）。实际上，社会可能必须做出广泛的改变才能适应人工智能。</p><h2>行业仍保持乐观</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/60fed960-176e-11ee-91ef-5acce9cb8167" style="height:1280px;width:1920px;" alt="Google DeepMind 的科林·默多克 (Colin Murdoch) 在 Collision 2023 上" data-uuid="d8a9bd7e-8987-3372-975c-94389063b87f"><figcaption>谷歌 DeepMind 首席商务官 Colin Murdoch 在 Collision 2023 上。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">乔恩·芬加斯/Engadget 摄</div></figure><h2></h2><p>Collision 的早期会谈充满希望。谷歌 DeepMind 业务主管科林·默多克 (Colin Murdoch) 在另一场讨论中表示，人工智能正在解决世界上一些最棘手的挑战。在这方面没有太多争议——DeepMind 正在编目<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/deepmind-ai-has-now-catalogued-every-protein-known-to-science-185116212.html">每一种已知的蛋白质</a></ins>，对抗抗生素耐药细菌，甚至加速相关工作<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/who-approves-first-malaria-vaccine-africa-191356314.html">疟疾疫苗</a></ins>。他设想了可以解决多种问题的“通用人工智能”，并以谷歌的产品为例。<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-03-13-google-lookout-app-us-release.html">小心</a></ins>对于描述照片很有用，但底层技术也使 YouTube Shorts 可以被搜索。默多克甚至称过去 6 到 12 个月是人工智能释放其潜力的“灯泡时刻”。</p><p> Roblox 首席科学家 Morgan McGuire 基本同意这一观点。他认为游戏平台的<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roblox-launches-its-first-generative-ai-game-creation-tools-192043349.html">生成式人工智能工具</a></ins>“缩小了新创作者和老手之间的差距”，使编写代码和创建游戏内材料变得更容易。 Roblox 甚至发布了一个开源人工智能模型 StarCoder，它希望通过使大型语言模型更易于访问来帮助其他人。虽然麦奎尔在一次讨论中承认在扩展和审核内容方面存在挑战，但他认为<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/facebook-metaverse-meta-explained-or-not-120032885.html">虚拟宇宙</a></ins>凭借其创意库，拥有“无限”的可能性。</p><p>默多克和麦奎尔都表达了与辛顿相同的一些担忧，但他们的语气显然不那么危言耸听。默多克强调 DeepMind 想要“安全、道德和包容”的人工智能，并指出专家咨询和教育投资就是证据。这位高管坚称，他对监管持开放态度，但前提是它允许“惊人的突破”。麦奎尔表示，Roblox 始终推出具有内容审核功能的生成式人工智能工具，依赖多样化的数据集并实行透明度。</p><h2>对未来有些许希望</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/020206c0-176f-11ee-b5fe-5e55ab8668b7" style="height:1280px;width:1920px;" alt="Roblox 的 Morgan McGuire 在 Collision 2023 上" data-uuid="2678ca11-a207-3cfd-8850-366c7217222c"><figcaption> Roblox 首席科学家 Morgan McGuire 在 Collision 2023 上发表讲话。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">乔恩·芬加斯/Engadget 摄</div></figure><h2></h2><p>尽管头条新闻总结了他最近的言论，但离开谷歌后，Hinton 对人工智能的整体热情并没有被浇灭。如果他没有放弃，他确信自己会致力于开发多模式人工智能模型，其中视觉、语言和其他线索有助于做出决策。 “小孩子不仅仅从语言中学习，”他说，并暗示机器也可以做同样的事情。尽管他担心人工智能的危险，但他相信人工智能最终可以做人类能做的任何事情，并且已经展示了“一点点推理能力”。例如，GPT-4 可以自我调整以解决更困难的难题。</p><p> Hinton 承认，他的《碰撞》演讲并没有过多谈论人工智能的良好用途，例如应对气候变化。人工智能技术的进步可能是健康的，即使仍然需要担心其影响。辛顿坦率地承认，尽管伦理和道德问题迫在眉睫，但他的热情并没有减弱。 “我喜欢这个东西，”他说。 “你怎么能不喜欢创造智能的东西呢？”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/ai-pioneer-geoffrey-hinton-isnt-convinced-good-ai-will-triumph-over-bad-ai-181536702.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/ai-pioneer-geoffrey-hinton-isnt-convinced-good-ai-will-triumph-over-bad-ai-181536702.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6b46eab0-8c6b-4099-834e-62dc7ab2b878</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2023 18:15:36 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688148644</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T18:10:59+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/7ee38c60-176d-11ee-9fbf-cb6f6652cddb" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/7ee38c60-176d-11ee-9fbf-cb6f6652cddb" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Ramsey Cardy/Collision via Sportsfile]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Geoffrey Hinton at Collision 2023]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Geoffrey Hinton at Collision 2023]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Tech firms sue Arkansas over social media age verification law]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>科技行业对阿肯色州<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-nintendo-switch-controllers-160034389.html">要求社交媒体年龄检查的</a>法律并不满意。包括谷歌、Meta 和 TikTok 在内的科技贸易集团 NetChoice <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://netchoice.org/netchoice-sues-arkansas-for-violating-the-first-amendment/">已起诉</a>阿肯色州，指控其《社交媒体安全法》违反美国宪法。据称，该措施要求用户交出私人数据才能访问社交网络，从而侵犯了第一修正案的言论自由权。 NetChoice 认为，它还“掌握了家庭的决策权”。</p><p>该联盟还认为，该法案使互联网公司依赖第三方服务来存储和跟踪儿童数据，从而损害了隐私和安全。 NetChoice 声称，州居民通常不知道或不参与该服务，而外部公司被认为是黑客攻击的“主要目标”。诉讼称，该法律试图在州法律之外监管互联网，同时无视联邦法律。由于阿肯色州无法在不需要数据的情况下验证居住权，因此它实际上要求每个人提交文件。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>州总检察长蒂姆·格里芬在一份声明中告诉 Engadget，他期待“大力捍卫”《社交媒体安全法》。法律要求通过提交驾驶执照和其他“商业上合理”的方法来验证所有用户的年龄。 18岁以下的人也需要得到父母的同意。 There are exceptions that appear to cover major social networks and their associated categories, such as those for &quot;professional networking&quot; (think LinkedIn) or short entertaining video clips (like TikTok).</p><p> Arkansas&#39; requirement is part of a <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/why-lawmakers-are-pushing-age-verification-requirements-for-social-media-platforms-190037563.html">greater trend among politicians</a> to demand age verification for social media. States <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/utah-passes-laws-requiring-parental-permission-for-teens-to-use-social-media-223302739.html">like Utah</a> , Connecticut and Ohio have either passed or are considering similar laws, while Senator Josh Hawley proposed a federal bill barring all social media access for kids under 16. They&#39;re concerned younger users might be exposed to <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/senate-hearing-tiktok-snapchat-youtube-204825470.html">creeps and inappropriate content</a> , and that use can <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/us-surgeon-general-says-social-media-can-pose-a-profound-risk-to-teens-mental-health-170517411.html">harm mental health</a> by presenting a skewed view of the world and encouraging addiction.</p><p> There&#39;s no guarantee the lawsuit will succeed. If it does, though, it could affect similar attempts to verify ages through personal data. If Arkansas&#39; approach is deemed unconstitutional, other states might have to drop their own efforts.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/tech-firms-sue-arkansas-over-social-media-age-verification-law-180002953.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/tech-firms-sue-arkansas-over-social-media-age-verification-law-180002953.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> b7a4d276-9dea-46f0-89ae-2cbb49dc58a2</guid><dc:creator> Jon Fingas</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 30 Jun 2023 18:00:02 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688147591</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T17:53:15+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="2796" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/14841a70-0751-11ec-a76d-aaba7904c41d" width="3919"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2796" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/14841a70-0751-11ec-a76d-aaba7904c41d" width="3919"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Dado Ruvic / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Facebook, TikTok, Twitter, YouTube and Instagram apps are seen on a smartphone in this illustration taken, July 13, 2021. REUTERS/Dado Ruvic/Illustration]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[TECH-SOCIALNETWORKS/]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Sega's COO says the company is not for sale]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Sega is not for sale, according to company COO Shuji Utsumi. The executive told <em>Bloomberg News</em> that the company<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-06-29/sega-coo-quashes-talk-of-microsoft-deal-in-favor-of-independence?sref=10lNAhZ9">isn&#39;t open to acquisition talks</a></ins> at the moment, despite rampant speculation that Microsoft was about to swoop in and force a shotgun wedding between Sonic and Master Chief.</p><p> Some of these rumors popped up due to a general consolidation trend in the gaming industry, with<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/embracer-group-gearbox-merger-aspyr-acquisition-154253122.html">big fish gobbling up everything in sight.</a></ins> Microsoft&#39;s one of the biggest fish of all and it&#39;s been many years since Sega sat on top of the gaming throne, despite remaining a solid developer and publisher. Also, a potential merger between Microsoft and Activision Blizzard led to the<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ftc-microsoft-activision-blizzard-antitrust-competition-lawsuit-191341476.html">FTC filing an antitrust lawsuit,</a></ins> which is ongoing. During the associated trial, it was revealed that Microsoft had many companies on its wishlist, including Sega. So the rumor mill continued unabated.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Utsumi declined to comment as to whether or not Microsoft approached Sega with an acquisition offer, but touted the “great relationship” between the two companies. This relationship has been on full display in recent years, with former Playstation exclusives from the Yakuza series to the Persona series showing up on Xbox consoles. A next-gen refresh of <em>Yakuza: Like a Dragon</em> was even an<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/yakuza-7-like-a-dragon-xbox-series-x-smart-delivery-202938026.html">Xbox Series X/S exclusive</a></ins> for a few months before going multi-platform.</p><p> The budding corporate friendship (aww) is extremely important to Microsoft, as Sega titles are popular in Japan and, well, Xbox consoles aren&#39;t. This is another reason the acquisition rumors spread so readily. However, Sega will remain as Sega Sammy Holdings for the time being, even if documents indicate that Microsoft was, at one point, ready to fork over serious cash to buy the house that Sonic built. Speaking of, there&#39;s a<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonic-superstars-gives-classic-gameplay-another-modern-makeover-200643371.html">new sidescrolling Sonic title</a></ins> launching later this year along with a<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/play-as-elephant-mario-in-super-mario-bros-wonder-on-october-20th-145814400.html">new sidescrolling Mario.</a></ins> What is this, 1991?</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/segas-coo-says-the-company-is-not-for-sale-174334550.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/segas-coo-says-the-company-is-not-for-sale-174334550.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0e9b8a38-87ad-4d48-b3ff-da1def712197</guid><dc:creator> Lawrence Bonk</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 30 Jun 2023 17:43:34 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688147015</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T17:43:42+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Mergers, Acquisitions & Takeovers]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="2402" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-06/a8bbae70-e8f0-11ec-b3e8-65230a13efe3" width="3500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2402" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-06/a8bbae70-e8f0-11ec-b3e8-65230a13efe3" width="3500"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Kim Kyung Hoon / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A model of Sega character 'Sonic the Hedgehog' is pictured at its headquarters in Tokyo, Japan, February 16, 2022. Picture taken on February 16, 2022. REUTERS/Kim Kyung-Hoon]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[SEGA SAMMY-SONIC/]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Twitter isn't showing tweets unless you're logged in]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> For some bizarre reason (OK,<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-stokes-confusion-as-verified-drama-continues-104321432.html">many</a></ins><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitters-head-of-safety-and-content-moderation-has-left-the-company-053113054.html">widely</a></ins><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-says-startups-can-experiment-with-its-data-for-5000-a-month-200705341.html">reported</a></ins><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/80-percent-of-twitters-full-time-staff-has-evaporated-under-musk-234247201.html">reasons</a></ins> ), Twitter is becoming less useful almost by the day. In its latest misstep, it seems the service is no longer letting people who aren&#39;t signed in see any tweets.</p><p> Until now, logged-out users were still able to check out tweets and user profiles, but at least for the time being, they&#39;ll have to either sign up for an account or plug in their login credentials to see whatever<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://kotaku.com/elon-musk-hard-drive-stolen-meme-twitter-credit-1848995870">unattributed meme</a></ins> Twitter owner Elon Musk pinched today.<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/30/23779764/twitter-blocks-unregistered-users-account-tweets"><em>The Verge</em></a> </ins><em>&nbsp;</em> spotted the issue, which Engadget has confirmed on multiple browsers and devices.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Twitter won&#39;t confirm whether this was a technical error or an intentional decision, as one of Musk&#39;s first moves after he took over the company was to all but wipe out its communications team. In any case, logged-out users haven&#39;t been able to use Twitter&#39;s search function<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://9to5mac.com/2023/04/26/twitter-restricts-search-fleets-coming-back/">since April</a></ins> 。</p><p> It&#39;s unclear what kind of impact moves such as this and<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-shut-off-its-free-api-and-its-breaking-a-lot-of-apps-222011637.html">Twitter&#39;s API changes</a></ins> will have on things like Google being able to include tweets in its search results. This could also prove a roadblock to services that scrape data from public-facing platforms like Twitter.</p><p> Making tweets visible only to signed-in users won&#39;t necessarily prompt people to sign up for an account. If someone wants to share a tweet with a person who doesn&#39;t use Twitter, they may now be more inclined to send a screenshot than a link, perhaps making it less likely that the non-user will join the service.</p><p> Researchers have found that most US adults are<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/us-adults-are-spending-less-time-on-twitter-since-elon-musk-took-over-192939586.html">spending less time on Twitter</a></ins> after Musk bought the service. You might think Twitter would be doing whatever it could to get more eyes on tweets and ads, given that its advertising revenue is<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitters-ad-sales-have-reportedly-dropped-by-59-percent-since-last-year-092543851.html">said to have plummeted</a></ins> 。 Putting up a barrier between potential new users and content perhaps isn&#39;t the wisest way to go about that.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/twitter-isnt-showing-tweets-unless-youre-logged-in-165254006.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/twitter-isnt-showing-tweets-unless-youre-logged-in-165254006.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> b07beaaf-9720-49e5-b0e2-730d87984cd2</guid><dc:creator> Kris Holt</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 30 Jun 2023 16:52:54 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688143975</ingested><modified> 2023-06-30T16:52:59+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="3700" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/56e07370-1765-11ee-bf7f-a2395af04909" width="5550"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3700" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/56e07370-1765-11ee-bf7f-a2395af04909" width="5550"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - The Twitter logo is seen on the awning of the building that houses the Twitter office in New York, Wednesday, Oct. 26, 2022. Twitter has dropped out of a voluntary European Union agreement to combat online disinformation, a top EU official said Friday, May 26, 2023. (AP Photo/Mary Altaffer, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Europe Twitter Disinformation]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best live TV streaming services in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Streaming promised us a world without cable contracts and the satisfaction of only paying for what we <em>actually</em> wanted to watch. But at what cost? Cutting the cord can mean you don&#39;t get to watch local channels, live sports or certain “cable only” networks. If you want to get back some of what cable has to offer – without signing a contract – a live TV streaming service may be what you need. We tested out six of the most popular offerings, comparing the features, prices and usability of each to come up with recommendations for different types of TV lovers.</p><h2> What to look for in a live TV streaming service</h2><h3> <strong>What you need to stream live TV</strong></h3><p> Streaming live TV is a lot like using Netflix. You get access through apps on your phone, tablet, smart TV, <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-streaming-devices-media-players-123021395.html">streaming device</a> , or a gaming system like an xBox or Playstation and the signal arrives over the internet. A faster and more stable internet connection tends to give you a better experience. Most live TV apps require you to sign up and pay via a web browser. After that, you can activate the app on your device.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h3><strong>价格</strong></h3><p>When I started my research, I was struck by the price difference between live TV and a <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-video-streaming-services-133000093.html">standard streaming app</a> like Netflix or Peacock. Where the latter cost between $5 and $20 per month, many live TV services hit around the $70 mark and can go higher than $100 with additional perks, channel packages and premium extras. I also learned that when it comes to base plans, higher price tags are mostly due to the cost of providing multiple networks – particularly sports and local stations.</p><h3> <strong>Local channels</strong></h3><p> Only two of the services we tried don&#39;t include full local channel coverage and one of those makes no effort at carrying sports. That would be Philo and, as you might guess, it&#39;s the cheapest. The next most affordable option, Sling, only carries three local stations, and only in larger markets, but it still manages to include some of the top sports channels.</p><p> When you sign up with any provider that handles local TV, you&#39;ll enter your zip code, ensuring you get your area&#39;s broadcast affiliates for ABC, CBS, FOX and NBC. Of course, you can also get those stations for free. Nearly all modern television sets support a radio frequency (RF) connection, also known as the coaxial port, which means if you buy an <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdNjSFySHUB5LvTxXF-PeO0y_Q2BikkE25wwz5DoNvP8&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FTV-Antenna-Indoor-Booster-Signal%2Fdp%2FB0BF9M8DVH">HD antenna</a> , you&#39;ll receive locally broadcast stations like ABC, CBS, FOX and NBC. And since the signal is digital, reception is much improved over the staticky rabbit-ears era.</p><h3><strong>运动的</strong></h3><p>One reality that spun my head was the sheer number and iterations of sports networks in existence. Trying to figure out which network will carry the match-up you want to see can be tricky. Google makes it a little easier for sports fans by listing out <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Google;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0931b986-736e-47bb-80b9-5f6f8f4ef5ae&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Google&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwOTMxYjk4Ni03MzZlLTQ3YmItODBiOS01ZjZmOGY0ZWY1YWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS9zZWFyY2g_cT11cGNvbWluZytuYmErZ2FtZXMiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAesTVaWGoJAGC8HeWPR-hONFNNDQi_RYK1Xsn7p9P7eQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dupcoming%2Bnba%2Bgames">upcoming games</a> : if you click on one, the “TV &amp; streaming” button will tell you which network is covering the event.</p><p> That just leaves figuring out if your chosen service carries that regional sports network. Unfortunately, even with add-ons and extra packages, some providers simply don&#39;t have certain channel lineups. It would take a lawyer to understand the ins and outs of <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/south-park-warner-bros-discovery-paramount-lawsuit-211615299.html">streaming rights negotiations</a> , and networks leave and return to live TV carriers all the time. That said, most major sporting events in the US are covered by ESPN, Fox Sports, TNT, USA and local affiliates. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/3cbec0e0-c42d-11ed-bfbe-961d0e86297a" alt="A TV displaying the logos for Philo, Sling, Hulu, DirecTV stream, fuboTV, and YouTube TV apps." data-uuid="745efd02-508c-3603-a480-547937b3d664"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Amy Skorheim / Engadget</div></figure><h3> <strong>Traditional cable networks</strong></h3><p> Dozens of networks were once only available with cable TV, like Bravo, BET, Food Network, HGTV, CNN, Lifetime, SYFY and MTV. If you only subscribe to, say, Max and Netflix, you won&#39;t have access to any of those. All the options we tested deliver sizable lists of cable networks, though only DirecTV gives you all of the top 36 channels ranked <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://sports.yahoo.com/126-cable-channels-ranked-2022-183059118.html">by Nielsen</a> as the most watched in 2022.</p><p> Media conglomerates continue to <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/warnermedia-discovery-merger-hbo-max-discovery-plus-214335645.html">merge</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/epix-relaunch-mgm-plus-140538789.html">rebrand</a> or reenter the streaming market, which means you can find many cable networks on traditional video streaming services like Peacock. Other channels like AMC+ have their own stand-alone apps. If you&#39;re just interested in live TV for cable-only shows, there are cheaper alternatives. I was particularly delighted by the 20 ad-free channels you get on the <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Discovery+;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=e3296106-c693-4525-ba0e-6b65767ea99e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Discovery%2B&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJlMzI5NjEwNi1jNjkzLTQ1MjUtYmEwZS02YjY1NzY3ZWE5OWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGlzY292ZXJ5cGx1cy5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAATxGz2ytnj6015YElXRvBTyedZd22GCfa43yqWiVYBRl&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.discoveryplus.com%2F">Discovery+</a> app for $7 per month. In addition to original content, Paramount+ has shows from multiple brands like MTV and Comedy Central, while Peacock has Bravo and Hallmark shows.</p><p> There&#39;s even a service called <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3RyeS5mcm5kbHl0di5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVsZIkFL_NAsojioaxhFb7VBEX8KUhX8w_0zsJABNpm3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Ftry.frndlytv.com%2F">Frndly TV</a> that costs a mere $7 per month and streams A&amp;E, Lifetime, Game Show Network, Vice and about 35 others. We didn&#39;t test it for this guide because it doesn&#39;t give you local access, news or sports and most people would be better served by the broader coverage on a cheap option like Philo.</p><p> I should also mention free ad-supported TV ( <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/youtube-is-testing-a-hub-of-free-cable-style-channels-192518784.html">FAST</a> ) streamers like <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.plex.tv/">Plex</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://tubitv.com/">Tubi</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://pluto.tv/welcome">PlutoTV</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tL2ZyZWVzdHJlYW0iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAcyvv1f4WLcVCmGT-rEGdv_2DOP0m5Yn54fVrXNGM8D4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2Ffreestream">Sling Freestream</a> that let you drop in and watch a decent selection of live networks at zero cost. Some don&#39;t even require a credit card. And if you have a Roku device or a Samsung TV, you can access hundreds of live channels via the <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Roku;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f3574a52-3bcf-4a37-83ee-65836ac78115&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Roku&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmMzU3NGE1Mi0zYmNmLTRhMzctODNlZS02NTgzNmFjNzgxMTUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucm9rdS5jb20vYmxvZy9saXZlLXR2LWNoYW5uZWwtZ3VpZGUiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASZfBxDz8Gv_hwIxJckRhMKzdWdnKp1y962ni-NMZTa9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.roku.com%2Fblog%2Flive-tv-channel-guide">Roku Channel</a> or through the <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmODVlNjNjZC1lMTNjLTRmOWQtOTkxYy05ZmJhYWRlZGUzYWMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vdXMvdGVsZXZpc2lvbnMtaG9tZS10aGVhdGVyL3R2cy90dnBsdXMvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdyIex31lMvycVVdw9tCy4RN348RUa9MCVRBRdvYCokU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Ftelevisions-home-theater%2Ftvs%2Ftvplus%2F">Samsung TV Plus</a> app.</p><h3> <strong>Digital video recordings (DVR)</strong></h3><p> Every option we&#39;ve included offers cloud DVR storage, so you don&#39;t need a separate physical device like you often do with traditional cable. You&#39;ll either get unlimited storage for recordings that expires after nine months or a year, or you&#39;ll get a set number of hours (between 50 and 1,000) that you can keep indefinitely. Typically, all you need to do is designate what you want to record and the DVR component will do all the hard work of saving subsequent episodes for you to watch later.</p><p> Aside from being able to watch whenever it&#39;s most convenient, you can also fast-forward through commercials in recorded content. In contrast, you can&#39;t skip them on live TV or video-on-demand (VOD).</p><p> Most live TV subscriptions include access to a selection of VOD content including movies and shows that are currently airing on your subscribed networks. This typically doesn&#39;t cover live events, local shows and news programming. But it does let you watch specific episodes of ongoing shows like <em>Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives</em> or BET&#39;s <em>Sistas</em> . Just search the on-demand library for the program, pick an episode and hit play.</p><h3> <strong>Tiers, packages and add-ons</strong></h3><p> Comparing price-to-offering ratios is a task for a spreadsheet. I… made three. The base plans range from $25 to $75 per month. From there, you can add on packages, which are usually groups of live TV channels bundled by themes like news, sports, entertainment or international. Those cost an extra $5 to $20 per month and simply show up in the guide where you find the rest of your base-level live TV.</p><p> Then there are more premium VOD add-ons, such as Max, AMC+, Starz or Showtime. You may already have these through standalone apps. If you don&#39;t, or if you prefer a combined bill and one access point for your streaming, many live TV subscriptions let you add them.</p><h2> How we tested</h2><p> When I begin testing for a guide, I research the most popular and well-reviewed players in the category and narrow down which are worth trying. For this space, just six services dominate, so I tried them all. After getting them set up using my laptop, I downloaded the apps on a Samsung smart TV running the latest version of Tizen OS. I counted the local stations and regional sports coverage, and noted how many of last year&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://sports.yahoo.com/126-cable-channels-ranked-2022-183059118.html">top cable networks</a> were available. I then weighed the prices, base packages and available add-ons.</p><p> I then looked at how the programming was organized in each app&#39;s UI and judged how easy everything was to navigate, from the top navigation to the settings. To test the search function, I searched for the same few TV shows on BET, Food Network, HGTV and Comedy Central, since all six providers carry those channels. I noted how helpful the searches were and how quickly they got me to season 6, episode 13 of <em>Home Town</em> .</p><p> I used DVR to record entire series and single movies and watched VOD shows, making sure to test the pause and scan functions. On each service with sports, I searched for the same four upcoming NHL, NBA, MLS and NCAA basketball matches and used the record option to save the games and play them back a day or two later. Finally, I noted any extra perks or irritating quirks.</p><p> Here&#39;s the full list of everything we tried:</p><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Philo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b250d7a0-0e4e-4332-bc87-bf6e669b0564&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Philo&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJiMjUwZDdhMC0wZTRlLTQzMzItYmM4Ny1iZjZlNjY5YjA1NjQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucGhpbG8uY29tL2xvZ2luL3N1YnNjcmliZSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAabIVZR19dFPFnrkXwC-HZhqdthhzjQEXtk-uUzjcKrv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.philo.com%2Flogin%2Fsubscribe">Philo</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAQuX1x-8Li1Y3BleLw5tlSNrUlv0th9PPvhRuDrLsSQD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2F">Sling</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://tv.youtube.com/welcome/">YouTube TV</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Hulu;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ca19dea0-e7ad-4f54-beed-6302bce56589&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Hulu&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjYTE5ZGVhMC1lN2FkLTRmNTQtYmVlZC02MzAyYmNlNTY1ODkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaHVsdS5jb20vbGl2ZS10diIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAASOsz4gSX7PSfobz14RykoXuU9OPnxuKEPPXAKT0mdHs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hulu.com%2Flive-tv">Hulu + Live TV</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:DIRECTV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=fd7207b2-1b6a-4385-aa15-2f04784de078&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=DIRECTV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmZDcyMDdiMi0xYjZhLTQzODUtYWExNS0yZjA0Nzg0ZGUwNzgiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGlyZWN0di5jb20vc3RyZWFtLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAZCwHkjcdTHbgJbx0h8bZZ50xk2YCKyUPzrRoo-1iCLq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.directv.com%2Fstream%2F">DirecTV Stream</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:FuboTV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=9a941868-c063-4b44-9207-896f1fb5891e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=FuboTV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI5YTk0MTg2OC1jMDYzLTRiNDQtOTIwNy04OTZmMWZiNTg5MWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cDovL3d3dy5mdWJvLnR2L3dlbGNvbWU_aXJhZD0zNDM3NDcmaXJtcD0yNTM2MjE3JnBhcnRuZXJwcm9wZXJ0eWlkPTMxNDI4MjMmc3ViSWQzPXhpZDpmcjE2NzQyNTQ5ODIwMDhiaGIiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAbfV5QVpXnp6Zv4vvSRE-0I6_ukuICBOH21I_DjeUyw3&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fubo.tv%2Fwelcome%3Firad%3D343747%26irmp%3D2536217%26partnerpropertyid%3D3142823%26subId3%3Dxid%3Afr1674254982008bhb">FuboTV</a></p></li></ul><h2> Most well-rounded: YouTube TV</h2><p><core-commerce id="5782c9e2123646cc8118d90a96ffb055" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Google&#39;s live TV streaming service has a lot of strengths. Compared to our top pick for sports, <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://tv.youtube.com/welcome/">YouTube TV</a> covers major and minor teams, regional games and national matchups almost as well. It gives you clear navigation, a great search function, unlimited DVR and broad network coverage. It&#39;s not quite as affordable as it once was, as YouTube recently <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/youtube-tv-raises-prices-to-an-outrageous-73-per-month-182517379.html">raised the price</a> to $73 per month – and it&#39;s even more financially precarious if you&#39;re not great at resisting temptation.</p><p> Upon signup, you&#39;re presented with nearly 50 different add-ons, including 4K resolution, premium channels and themed packages. Even if you fight the urge to roll Max, Shudder and AcornTV into the mix at signup, the enticement remains as it&#39;s dangerously easy to add more to your subscription. If you search for a program on a network you don&#39;t have, you&#39;re prompted to add it. And of course, you can also rent or buy movies that aren&#39;t currently showing on any channels, just like you can via YouTube. While it&#39;s convenient to be able to order up anything you might want on a whim, I imagine this pushes many users&#39; bills far above Google&#39;s listed $73 per month.</p><p> Still, it&#39;s nice to have all your entertainment in one place. And if you <em>only</em> want the add-ons, you can actually subscribe to most of the standalone networks without paying for the base plan. Either way, you get a familiar user experience, with navigation you&#39;ll recognize if you&#39;ve spent any time on regular ol&#39; YouTube. Unsurprisingly, Google&#39;s search function was the best of the bunch, finding the shows and games I searched for quickly and giving me clear choices for how to watch and record.</p><p> At signup, you&#39;ll also pick the shows, networks and teams you like, which are added to your library. YouTube TV then automatically records them. You get unlimited cloud DVR space (though recordings expire after nine months) and it&#39;s dead simple to add programming to your library. Like a real cable experience, YouTube TV autoplays your last-watched program upon startup by default, but it was the only service that allowed me to turn that feature off by heading to the settings.</p><p> Searching for and recording an upcoming game was easy. Once the game was recorded, I had to hunt a little to find it in my library (turns out single games are listed under the Events heading, not Sports). But after that, playback was simple and included a fascinating extra feature: You can either play a recorded game from the beginning or hit Watch Key Plays. The latter gives you between 12 and 20 highlight snippets, each about 10 seconds long. It focuses on the most impressive shots in an NBA bout and includes every goal in an MLS matchup. The feature was available for NCAA basketball and in-season major American leagues (hockey, soccer and basketball at the time of testing). Foreign and more minor games didn&#39;t have the feature.</p><p> Sports fans will also appreciate the new multiview feature that YouTube TV added earlier this year that lets you pick up to four sports, news and weather channels from a select list and view them all at the same time on your screen. If you find yourself constantly flipping back and forth between games, this could save you some hassle.</p><p> YouTube TV also gives you the most in-app settings. You can add parental controls to a profile or pull up a stats menu that shows your buffer health and connection speeds. You can lower playback resolution for slow connections and even send feedback to YouTube. It was also the best at integrating VOD and live programming. For example, if you search for a show that happens to be playing live, a red badge in the corner of the show&#39;s image lets you know it&#39;s on right now. Other services didn&#39;t display this info as clearly.</p><p> Now that YouTube TV is $73 per month, it&#39;s no longer cheaper than <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Hulu;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ca19dea0-e7ad-4f54-beed-6302bce56589&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Hulu&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjYTE5ZGVhMC1lN2FkLTRmNTQtYmVlZC02MzAyYmNlNTY1ODkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaHVsdS5jb20vbGl2ZS10diIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAASOsz4gSX7PSfobz14RykoXuU9OPnxuKEPPXAKT0mdHs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hulu.com%2Flive-tv">Hulu + Live TV</a> , which is $70. And if you already subscribe to the regular Hulu app, this is definitely the better better choice. Hulu&#39;s option gives you live TV streaming, plus all of Hulu&#39;s content, some of which you can&#39;t get elsewhere.</p><p> Hulu + Live TV carries your local affiliates and 32 of the top 36 cable channels, which is the same number as YouTube TV. For sports, you get all available ESPN iterations plus FS1, FS2, TBS, USA, TNT, NBC Golf and the NFL Network. You can also add on premium VOD channels like Max and Showtime, and it&#39;s the only provider that includes Disney+ at no extra cost.</p><p> Navigation on Hulu + Live TV isn&#39;t as smooth as most of the other options – it felt like the live component had been shoehorned into the standard Hulu app. But if you&#39;re already comfortable with (and paying for) Hulu, upgrading to the live TV bundle might be worthwhile.</p><p> <strong>YouTube TV</strong></p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $73/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: Yes</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 32 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: Unlimited, 9-month expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 6</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: 3 (unlimited with upgrade)</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: Yes</p></li></ul><p> <strong>Hulu + Live TV</strong></p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $70/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: Yes</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 32 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: Unlimited, 9-month expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 6</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: 2 (unlimited with upgrade)</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: No</p></li></ul><h2> Best cable without a contract: DirecTV Stream</h2><p><core-commerce id="098b5d0272e54a0db7837a7ed79bc0b5" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Canceling cable is <a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/brooklynninenine/comments/cgt6nq/i_need_you_to_cancel_my_cable/">no joke</a> – those contracts are <em>binding</em> . But if you enjoy the serendipity of flipping from one channel to the next and having access to as many networks as possible, <a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N0cmVhbXR2LmRpcmVjdHYuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAdcf5W3Vm5-FJv1zdJ3KP6SN7FzIWHiSqW07po7lGxqU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fstreamtv.directv.com%2F">DirecTV Stream</a> will give you a very similar experience to cable without shackling you to a contract. Like cable, it allows you to jump to the “next” sequential channel (yes, DirecTV Stream numbers its channels) with a single button press, transforming the left and right d-pad buttons of a smart TV remote into the rocker on a standard clicker.</p><p> It carries all the top 36 cable networks (though Game Show Network and Animal Planet are only available at the second tier and above) and lets you add multiple packages and premiums like Showtime, Starz, AMC+ and Discovery+. You can also add Max, just like on YouTube TV and Hulu + Live TV, but DirecTV is the only one we tried that lets you add Peacock. Of course, you can always add those apps separately to your smart TV, but for anyone who prefers the all-in-one convenience of cable, it&#39;s a nice perk.</p><p> When you fire up DirecTV Stream, whichever network you last watched automatically starts playing. It continues when you switch over to the guide or other menu pages. If you&#39;re used to the quieter experience of traditional streaming apps (after you turn off <a data-i13n="cpos:30;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-06-netflix-autoplay-preview-settings.html">autoplay</a> ), you might find that a little distracting.</p><p> The navigation didn&#39;t feel intuitive, partly because the menu options overlay the currently playing show and because there are so many ways to browse, access and control live, recorded and on-demand content. The search function was the least integrated of the services I tested. Instead of live-suggesting as you type, it forces you to enter your full search term on a separate keyboard interface. Even with that limitation, it found the shows and movies I searched for and accurately presented the upcoming games I wanted just from typing in one of the teams.</p><p> You can&#39;t add new channels or packages through the app, which might be a relief to anyone worried about succumbing to subscription overload. Everyone else may just find it annoying.</p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $75/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: Yes</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 36 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: Unlimited, 9-month expiration (maximum of 30 episodes per series)</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 1</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: Unlimited</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: No</p></li></ul><h2> Best for live sports: FuboTV</h2><p><core-commerce id="c1c7aed949a941bf8836667bc394688b" data-type="product-list"></p><p> When you first sign up for <a data-i13n="cpos:31;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:FuboTV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=9a941868-c063-4b44-9207-896f1fb5891e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=FuboTV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI5YTk0MTg2OC1jMDYzLTRiNDQtOTIwNy04OTZmMWZiNTg5MWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnViby50di93ZWxjb21lIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAd2jf7G-Y7GYxiqagnhDJbE-y7bjBQ2o8NrishZ2kMs7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fubo.tv%2Fwelcome">FuboTV</a> , it asks what teams you follow across all kinds of sports. Pick teams from in-season leagues and you&#39;ll quickly have DVR content to watch. That&#39;s because Fubo records every game your teams play as long as it&#39;s aired on a supported channel – and its sports coverage is vast.</p><p> I tested out a premium subscription and the guide said there were 118 sports networks to choose from. In addition to the usual suspects from ESPN, Fox, NBC and CBS, you can watch motorsports, international leagues, adventure sports and even poker. Add-ons give you NBA TV, NHL Network, NFL Red Zone and MLB Network. And if you need access to all one thousand games the NBA plays in a season, you can add the NBA League Pass to your lineup for $15 per month. FuboTV even has its <em>own</em> sports channels.</p><p> Yes, the coverage is comprehensive, but FuboTV also made finding and recording specific games very easy. Searching for an upcoming game was simple, as was sifting through the ample amount of recorded games I ended up with. I particularly liked FanView for live games, which inserts the video into a smaller window and surrounds that window with continually updating stats plus a clickable list of other games currently airing.</p><p> FuboTV has made an obvious effort to win at sports, but recently it&#39;s tried to deliver on the live TV experience as well. Based on what I&#39;ve seen so far, it&#39;s certainly made strides. The guide was impressive in the number of ways it let you organize live TV, yet everything felt clean and uncluttered. The Home, Sports, Shows and Movies pages were filled with recommendations and many iterations of categories, with almost all suggestions being live TV.</p><p> Where FuboTV falls short is in VOD access and DVR playback. It wasn&#39;t the best at finding the shows I searched for, and navigating available VOD content wasn&#39;t as breezy as browsing through live programming. The lack of a pop-up preview window as you fast forward or rewind through recordings makes it tough to gauge where you are in a show. As for price, FuboTV ties with DirecTV Stream for the most expensive base package at $75. But if you need <em>all</em> the sports – and want some nicely organized live TV during the few moments when there&#39;s not a game on – this is the way to go.</p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $75/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: Yes</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 29 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: 1000 hours, no expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 6</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: 10</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: Yes (Apple TV only)</p></li></ul><h2> Most customizable: Sling TV</h2><p><core-commerce id="735b4ade5df448b598929743f894ed90" data-type="product-list"></p><p> To me, the idea of spending time fine-tuning channel choices sounds exhausting. But if you&#39;re the type who wants to get exactly what you want without paying for too much of what you don&#39;t, <a data-i13n="cpos:32;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAQuX1x-8Li1Y3BleLw5tlSNrUlv0th9PPvhRuDrLsSQD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2F">Sling TV</a> may be your best bet. It breaks its base plan into two packages, Blue and Orange, with different channels on each. Blue, which costs $45 a month, carries a larger number of networks, while Orange seems to have spent its lineup dollars on ESPN and ESPN 2. But at $40 monthly, Sling Orange is the cheapest way to get those two sports outlets.</p><p> After picking a plan, you can choose from a stable of add-on packages, with monthly prices ranging from $6 to $11. These include blocks of sports or lifestyle channels, kid-friendly fare, the Discovery+ bundle and a news package. There are 46 individual premium offerings, including Showtime, Starz, MGM+, Shudder and Acorn, which go for between $2 and $10 per month. Sling has pay-per-view movies, too.</p><p> As far as local coverage, Sling Blue grants access to ABC, Fox and NBC local affiliates in about 20 of the larger US markets including Los Angeles, Seattle, Dallas, NYC, Miami and DC. ABC coverage began in March 2023, but unfortunately, that raised the price of Sling Blue in supported markets from $40 to $45. For people not in those areas (or who opt for Orange) Sling is currently running a <a data-i13n="cpos:33;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tL3Byb2dyYW1taW5nL2xvY2FsLWNoYW5uZWxzIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAe_a43827fNAzxdGbME6_g1Hxe1vYDxKcViw1EF1Ygsr&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2Fprogramming%2Flocal-channels">promotion</a> for a free HD antenna to catch local stations.</p><p> Navigation is speedy and the interface is nicely organized, putting an emphasis on what you like to watch, with recommendations that are pretty accurate. The UI also makes the add-ons you&#39;ve chosen easy to find. In my tests, though, the app froze a number of times as I navigated. While most services froze once or twice, it happened enough times with Sling to frustrate me. I had to force quit or back out of the app and start over five or six times during the three weeks of testing. Compared to others, Sling&#39;s DVR allowance is on the stingy side, only giving you 50 hours of recordings, though they won&#39;t expire. You can pay for more DVR storage, but that will increase your overall costs.</p><p> I tried not to wander too far off-path during testing, but I feel it&#39;s my duty to inform you that Sling has an Elvis channel, a Bob Ross channel and ALF TV (yes, an entire station devoted to the &#39;80s sitcom starring a puppet). There&#39;s also a <a data-i13n="cpos:34;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5kb2d0di5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAfLLpz7B5Fdqmc2tN7mcDJLtJxgZvqFBK5LMTZRrKyJU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dogtv.com%2F">Dog TV network</a> intended to be played for your dogs when you leave the house, which you can add to Sling or get as a standalone app.</p><ul><li><p> Base plan: Starting at $40/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: ABC, FOX, NBC in limited markets</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 22 or 29 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: 50 hours, no expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 4</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: 1 or 3</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: Yes</p></li></ul><h2> Best budget: Philo</h2><p><core-commerce id="9a1b66d1fc8b4bc9b2dd8a614d94dacd" data-type="product-list"></p><p> At just $25 per month, <a data-i13n="cpos:35;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Philo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b250d7a0-0e4e-4332-bc87-bf6e669b0564&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Philo&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJiMjUwZDdhMC0wZTRlLTQzMzItYmM4Ny1iZjZlNjY5YjA1NjQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucGhpbG8uY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAdsHmIjh3zVIRyP2fviwnS5u08Acnwz0UTQ3mtTL48ip&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.philo.com%2F">Philo</a> is one of the cheapest ways to get a cordless live TV experience. The biggest caveat is that you won&#39;t find any local stations or sports programming on it. If that&#39;s not an issue, Philo is great, with a clean, streamlined interface and generous DVR limits.</p><p> I&#39;m a fan of minimalist design, so I appreciated the way Philo presented its menus and guide. There are just four top navigation headings: Home, Guide, Saved and Search. And instead of the usual guide layout that stretches out or shortens a show&#39;s listing to represent its air time, Philo&#39;s guide features monospaced squares in chronological order with the duration of the program inside the square. Another nice touch is when you navigate to a square, it fills with a live video of the show or movie.</p><p> Philo doesn&#39;t limit the amount of programming you can DVR and lets you keep recordings for a full year, which is more than the nine months other providers allow. Like all live TV streamers, Philo won&#39;t let you fast forward VOD programming. If skipping commercials is important to you, I recommend taking advantage of that unlimited DVR policy and hitting “Save” on any show or movie you think you may want to watch, then fast forwarding it on playback (you can do this with all the services we tried).</p><p> As far as channels, Philo covers 23 of the top 36 cable networks, with notable exceptions including Fox News, CNN, ESPN and MSNBC. Anyone looking for great news coverage should look elsewhere anyway, but the lack of a few must-have entertainment outlets like Bravo and Freeform was a little disappointing.</p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $25/mo.</p></li><li><p> Local channels: No</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 23 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: Unlimited, one year expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 10</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous streams: 3</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: Yes (browser only)</p></li></ul> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-live-tv-streaming-service-133000410.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-live-tv-streaming-service-133000410.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 50eb34db-c0fc-4bfb-ab41-1cbe97faffd8</guid><dc:creator> Amy Skorheim</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 30 Jun 2023 16:45:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688143510</ingested><m